node.text:
Hi guys! Long time no new posts from me, 
I missed posting here and talking to you! 💕🥺
This is the latest illustration I painted for the winner of the @calpico.usa CALPICO new flavor contest! 
The melon flavor was chosen as their new flavor by voting from CALPICO fans at the CALPICO Contest flavor stage. I also voted for melon flavor so was super happy to draw this :D
Now they are at the bottle design stage and the design contest is starting now! 
You can submit your original CALPICO bottle design for the chance to win prizes or even possibly have your design in stores! *v*
Follow this link: https://contest2021.calpico-usa.com/package-design-contest/
to take part. You could win some awesome prizes and your design could become
available in stores next summer! 
Thank you CALPICO for hosting such awesome giveaways! ❤️
.
.
.

Giveaway is now closed! The winner is @maria.oris_art 🎉
Cozy workspace ❤️ Made this illustration with the new XP-PEN (Artist22 2nd Generation) tablet I kindly received from @xppen 
@xppen and I are now making a GIVEAWAY for you guys so one lucky winner will get this exact tablet! Please check out the rules to enter! 🤗
⭐️ You have to be following my account as well as @xppen_ca and @xppen_usa 
⭐️ Share this post in your story
⭐️ Tag a friend in the comments 
And that’s it! 
The giveaway will be closing on May 21 and on May 22 we will announce the winner! 
(The winner will have to pay the customs duties themselves if applicable. Shipping is not available to Africa, the Middle East, South America, India, and some island countries.)
So for this illustration I decided to draw similar to how my workspace looks like except I don’t have two cats but one shih-tzu 💕 Here’s my review of the tablet! It’s the first time I was drawing on such a huge tablet screen so at first it felt almost intimidating but I very quickly got used to it. The biggest pros for me was definitely that it has a very sturdy and adjustable stand, you can freely change the screen's angle as you wish. Also, they reduced the number of control/supply cables in comparison to their previous models which is a huge improvement and much more user friendly! Also really love how the colors looks almost exactly the same as on my pc and how the screen quickly reacts to my pen movements! All in all I really recommend it and I’ve been using it daily since I got it. I think it’s a great price for such a product honestly. If you’re interested, you can use my code “Artist222nd” for a 5% discount. Here’s the direct link: https://www.storexppen.ca/buy/artist-cd220f.html?channel=toshiasan or https://www.storexppen.com/buy/artist-cd220f.html?channel=toshiasan 
Thanks @xppen for this opportunity!
.
.
.
